DUBAI: Clubhouse is a new voice only social media app that’s currently making waves. If you’ve managed to secure an invite, read on for the Arab stars you should follow. For the latest updates, follow us on Instagram @arabnews.lifestyle Jessica Kahawaty A post shared by Jessica Kahawaty جيسيكا قهواتي (@jessicakahawaty) The Lebanese-Australian model and humanitarian is also the founder of Mama Rita, a food delivery concept which she launched alongside her mother Rita Kahawaty in 2020.  Rania Fawaz A post shared by RANIA (@raniafawazz) The Dubai-based Iraqi fashion influencer has gained an impressive following on social media for her head-turning fashion sense and down-to-earth personality.  Mona Kattan A post shared by Mona Kattan (@monakattan) The younger sister of beauty mogul Huda Kattan, Mona is an entrepreneur in her own right and founded fragrance line Kayali as well as Dubai-based beauty salon, Dollhouse. Lana El-Sahely A post shared by Lana El Sahely لانا الساحلي (@lanaelsahely) Hailing from Lebanon, the fashion influencer is also an entrepreneur — she’s the founder of e-commerce platform larmoiredelana.com. The fashion star also dabbles in modeling from time to time, having walked for Dolce & Gabbana during Milan Fashion Week and fronting a Vogue Japan cover in 2017.  Arwa Al-Banawi A post shared by ARWA AL BANAWI (@arwaalbanawi) The Saudi contemporary womenswear designer is known for creating expertly-tailored pant suits that serve to empower the women that wear them.  Razane Jammal A post shared by Razane Jammal رزان جمّال (@razanejammal) Born and raised in Beirut, the Lebanese actress is best known for her roles in Olivier Assayas’ “Carlos,” Tobe Hooper’s “Djinn” and Netflix original series “Paranormal.” 